<TITLE> 'Close associate' of Mufti Hannan arrested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 29 (bdnews24.com)Police arrested an alleged close associate of the leader of the banned militant outfit Harkatul-Jihad-al-Islami, Bangladesh (HUJI-B), Mufti Abdul Hannan, in Shyampur in the capital Tuesday night. The arrestee, 43-year-old Sheikh Shahajahan, however, denied any link to Mufti Hannan , police said. Shyampur police sub-inspector Zillur Rahman told bdnews24.com Werdnesday that on information they arrested him at a workshop on Nabin Chandra Road. Shahajahan is being sought by police in Sylhet in a murder case, he said. Zillur also said that the militants tried to kill Awami league chief and prime minister Sheikh Hasina at a public rally in Sylhet in Sept, 2001 but failed. Later they exploded bombs at the residence of another militant, Rifat, which left two killed, he said The police pressed charges accusing Mufti Hannan and Shahajahan, among others. Shahajahan told reporters Wednesday he was not involved in the Sylhet killing because he had been in jail in another case at that time. He also claimed to have never seen Mufti Hannan nor had spoken to him. b
